SIMPLE: decoration
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: decoration
<hw>dec`o*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(d⟦ecr⟧k`⟦osl⟧*r⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL. <ets>decoratio</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧coration</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
adorning, embellishing, or honoring; ornamentation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which adorns, enriches, or beautifies;
something added by way of embellishment; ornament.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The hall was celebrated for . . . the richness of its
<qex>decoration</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Specifically, any mark of honor to be worn upon the
person, as a medal, cross, or ribbon of an order of knighthood, bestowed
for services in war, great achievements in literature, art,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decoration Day</ent>⟦br⟧
